% ======================================================================
%  Auburn University Research Poster -- accessible (PDF/UA-1 tagged)
%  THEME: Deep Space -- the poster IS the night sky. Dark-ground design:
%  deep-space ink page, moonlight-white text, star-gold accents, nebula
%  glows, a full starfield with bright "star lanes" running down the
%  column gutters, a shooting star, and along the bottom an observatory
%  horizon: teal dawn-glow, a domed observatory with a lit slit, pine
%  silhouettes, and a rising moon. The one highlighted panel is INVERTED
%  relative to the light themes: the theorem sits on the poster's single
%  BRIGHT card -- the full moon of the page. The three figures are
%  dark-ground variants (regenerated by figures/make-figures.py) whose
%  surfaces glow above the page ink, with star-gold line work.
%
%  One clear mathematical idea: 120 x 72 cm landscape, three columns
%  with a centre-stage hierarchy -- the main theorem in the ONLY bright
%  panel above one strong visual (the Calabi-Yau quintic surface).
%
%  Because this poster is a plain article (not beamer), it compiles to
%  a REAL tagged, PDF/UA-1 conformant PDF: reading order, language, and
%  the logo, figures, and QR code tagged as Figures with alt text.
%  (The QR code sits on a small bright card: inverted QR codes scan
%  poorly, so the modules stay dark-on-light even on this dark page.)
%
%  COMPILE WITH LuaLaTeX:
%    * Overleaf:  Menu -> Compiler -> LuaLaTeX, then Recompile.
%    * Locally:   latexmk
% ======================================================================
\NeedsTeXFormat{LaTeX2e}
\ProvidesPackage{postertheme}[2026/07/04 poster-research-deepspace poster theme]


